I have just upgraded my project from cocos2d-x v3.7 up to v3.9 release and discovered problem with Button widget. I have button with 9-slice enabled created with cocostudio. And after cloning button it displayed with wrong size - width and height of button are equal to texture size, not the original button size.

Without these lines of code everything working perfect:

```
UIButton.cpp
void Button::setupNormalTexture() {
    ...
    // force update _customSize, fixed issue:
    // https://github.com/cocos2d/cocos2d-x/issues/12249
    _customSize = _normalTextureSize;
    ... 
}
```

It can be reproduced with cocos2d-x v3.9, cocostudio 2.3.3 (mac os). If it's important texture was packed in atlas with TexturePacker.

```
auto rootNode = cocos2d::CSLoader::createNode("Layers/UILayer.csb");
addChild(rootNode);

auto btn = rootNode->getChildByName<cocos2d::ui::Button*>("btn");
auto btn2 = btn->clone();
addChild(btn2);
btn2->setPositionY(btn->getPositionY() + 100);
```

<img width="228" alt="screen shot 2015-12-05 at 16 17 26" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2494560/11607986/e71566d4-9b6d-11e5-90c3-20899730da07.png">

Following guard block for checking blank file name is removed from `AbstractCheckButton::loadTextureBackGroundSelected()` at 27f6d6a6ba6f39cbffc0c12999f9e510077266dd.

```
#ifndef CC_STUDIO_ENABLED_VIEW   // for cocostudio only
    if (backGroundSelected.empty())
    {
        return;
    }
#endif
```

This causes that any check button cannot be created without background selected image.

The commit 27f6d6a6ba6f39cbffc0c12999f9e510077266dd removed several checking logics. It needs to be reviewed again.
